HEADWORD: Sainted
<hw>Saint"ed</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Consecrated; sacred;
holy; pious.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧A most <xex>sainted</xex> king.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Amongst the enthroned gods on <qex>sainted</qex> seats.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Entered into heaven; -- a euphemism for
<altname>dead</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Saintess</ent>⟦br⟧
